{"author":{"id":"471db39b7744d7ac391a3fce7e6762bab4233e0bccb2a6ed236078e1bcc1f174"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1623765107,"nonce":"oVe4Ft+cuyiahYjw0IGj8cCQuoU=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDg2MTUxNjc3MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/672#issuecomment-861516770"},"message":"This is the function I have come up with for my own purposes:\n\n```python\ndef get_data_location(dandiset_id, filepath, s3=False):\n    \"\"\"Get the location for any NWB file on DANDI\"\"\"\n    \n    asset_id = requests.request(\n        \"GET\",\n        f\"https://api.dandiarchive.org/api/dandisets/{dandiset_id}/versions/draft/assets/\",\n        headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"},\n        params={\"path\": filepath},\n    ).json()['results'][0]['asset_id']\n    \n    url = f\"https://api.dandiarchive.org/api/dandisets/{dandiset_id}/versions/draft/assets/{asset_id}/download/\"\n    if not s3:\n        return url\n    \n    s3_url = requests.request(url=url, method='head').url\n    if '?' in s3_url:\n        return s3_url[:s3_url.index('?')]\n    return s3_url\n```\n\nI have found it useful to add this flag for whether I want to forward on to the blob url. For streaming you need the s3 url, but the download url is better for downloading because the file name is preserved.","files":null}]}